name: ^ hbc point blanket (SOLD)
description:
A vintage Hudson Bay Company three and a half point wool blanket.

The label has mostly come off but there's enough left to see it was an original.

Origins:

For over two centuries the Hudson's Bay Company point blanket has been a familiar item in Canada and around the world. It is enjoyed as much today as when it was first introduced into the fur trade in 1780. It is believed that M. Germain Maugenest first suggested to the Company's London Committee that "pointed blankets" become a regular trade item. The "point" system had been invented by French weavers in the mid 18th c. as a means of indicating the finished overall size (area) of a blanket, since then, as now, blankets were shrunk or felted as part of the manufacturing process. The word point derives from the French empointer meaning "to make threaded stitches on cloth". Pointed blankets quickly became very popular with the aboriginal peoples.

name: ^ hand-stitched RAF tribute
description:
Vintage hand-stitched Winston Churchill tribute to the Royal Air Force.

This is a beautifully aged and delicate piece of work.

The evacuation of Dunkirk, codenamed Operation Dynamo, took place between 26 May and 4 June 1940.
A flotilla of 900 naval and civilian craft was sent across the Channel under RAF protection and managed to rescue 338,226 people.
During the evacuation, the Luftwaffe attacked whenever the weather allowed, reducing the town of Dunkirk to rubble and destroying 235 vessels and 106 aircraft.

Wanderer above the Mist (1818)
This well-known and especially Romantic masterpiece was described by the writer John Lewis Gaddis as leaving a contradictory impression, "suggesting at once mastery over a landscape and the insignificance of the individual within it. name: ^ cabinet stereo  (SOLD)
description:
'Nordmende Caruso Spezial' cabinet stereo from 1962. 
This stereo was originally made in Germany, but was exported to Cuba (hence the "spezial" label) and has since made its way to Canada. Nordmende was one in a line of excellent German stereo companies of the era including Grundig and Telefunkin.

The stereo features Broadcast, Shortwave, Long wave and FM and it comes with an original 'Dual' turntable.

Sounds great and functions wonderfully.

Unlike most American cabinet stereos this European model is modest in size and may double as a shelf.
